# S3 data protection

## Versioning

Every PUT/DELETE kept; a delete adds a **delete marker** (prior versions live underneath). Once on → only **suspended, never disabled**. Versions cost storage → expire non-current via lifecycle.

- **MFA Delete** (root-only) — MFA to purge a version
- **Object Lock** — **WORM**, no change/delete for a retention period → compliance

## Replication (async, to another bucket)

- **CRR** (cross-region) — DR, latency, residency · **SRR** (same-region) — logs, cross-account
- Both buckets need **versioning** + a service role

**Doesn't by default:** backfill existing (→ Batch Replication) · replicate delete markers · chain (A→B→C) · Glacier objects.
